  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then boil a kettle</p><p>Peel the<strong> potatoes</strong> and cut them into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop the <strong>Brussels sprouts</strong> into quarters</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for an initial 10 min, then add the <strong>sprouts</strong> and cook for 2-3 min further or until everything is fork tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1668074696451-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1668074696451-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1668074696451-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1668074696451-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1668074696451-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes and sprouts are done, drain and return them to the pot</p><p>Meanwhile, reboil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1668074716316-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1668074716316-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1668074716316-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1668074716316-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1668074716316-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>,<strong> carrot </strong>and <strong>garlic </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve the<strong> beef stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and stir in the <strong>Marmite</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1668074725852-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1668074725852-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1668074725852-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1668074725852-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1668074725852-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, add the <strong>beef mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Once the beef is browned, add the<strong> tomato stock </strong>to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Season with a grind of<strong> pepper </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until slightly thickened – this is your <strong>beef mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1668074742742-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1668074742742-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1668074742742-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1668074742742-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1668074742742-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the beef mixture thickens, return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> and <strong>sprouts</strong> to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, a splash of <strong>milk </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mash until smooth – this is your <strong>sprout mash</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1668074755896-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1668074755896-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
